<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE en-export SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/evernote-export2.dtd"><en-export export-date="20130826T134736Z" application="Evernote/Windows" version="4.x"><note><title>mphasis (HP) #391</title><content><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note style="background: #cccccc;font-family: 'Helvetica Neue',  Helvetica, Arial, 'Liberation Sans', FreeSans, sans-serif;color: #585957;font-size: 14px;line-height: 1.3;"><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>            <!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd">            <en-note style="word-wrap: break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; -webkit-line-break: after-white-space;">            #Benefits <BR/><BR/>Benefit Details:<BR/> <BR/>Vacation:<BR/>2 weeks paid vacation(10 Days)<BR/>3 Days sick leave<BR/> <BR/>Benefits<BR/>Health plans, Life Insurance and Disability Coverage<BR/>Single -$75 per month<BR/>Employee + Partner: $150 per month<BR/>Employee & Child(ren) : $100 per month<BR/>Family: $300 per month<BR/> <BR/>Note: For more details please refer to attachment.<BR/> <BR/> <BR/>Mphasis offers the following benefits to eligible employees:<BR/>PPO<BR/>Medical Insurance<BR/>Prescription Insurance (RX)<BR/>Dental Insurance and<BR/>Vision Plan<BR/> <BR/>Mphasis will provide the eligible employees with details on these plans at the time of joining Mphasis in the United States.<BR/> <BR/>Relocation<BR/>Married Employees will be eligible to avail  relocation allowance based on actual expenditure incurred up to a maximum of $3000.<BR/>Single Employees will be eligible to avail an relocation allowance based on  actual expenditure incurred up to a maximum of $2000.<BR/> <BR/>All claims will have to be supported by Bills/Vouchers and a single claim lodged for all transfer cost expenses.<BR/>In addition, employee will also be eligible for reimbursement for any expense towards lease breakage, up to a maximum of 1 month rent or $1500 where CCA is greater or equal to $8000 per annum OR $1000 where CCA is less than $8000 per annum  whichever is lesser. Immediate Supervisor/Project Manager approves it (This will have to be supported by a copy of the lease agreement and receipt by the Apartment office).<BR/> <BR/>Accommodation POLICY<BR/>Employees relocating within the US will be eligible for a one time subsidized accommodation provided by the Company for a period of four (4) weeks, the details of which are given below:<BR/>1.Where City Compensatory Allowance (CCA) is greater than or equal to $ 8000 per annum  Employees need to pay $ 60 per day, balance would be paid by the Company<BR/>2.Where City Compensatory Allowance (CCA) is lesser than $ 8000 per annum  Employees need to pay $ 40 per day, balance would be paid by the Company<BR/>3.This amount will be deducted from US salary on a monthly basis, depending upon the duration of stay. This one time four-week subsidized accommodation can only be availed by the employees immediately upon relocation to the new location. On completion of the above duration, employees need to look out for their own accommodation.<BR/> <BR/>One way Air fare for you and family.<BR/>             </en-note></en-note>]]></content><created>20130513T064224Z</created><updated>19700101T053007Z</updated><tag>benefits</tag></note></en-export>
